Prior to the longitudinal analysis the `annotation` module from PHROAGER (https://github.com/aponsero/PHORAGER) was used for QC of predicted proviral sequences.
I have included the scripts for manually running CheckV (https://bitbucket.org/berkeleylab/checkv), Pharokka (https://github.com/gbouras13/pharokka) and PHOLD (https://github.com/gbouras13/phold)
and processing of outputs (see 02_viral_QC).

If you would like to avoid completing each step manually, please run PHORAGER.

First, geNomad (see 01_prophage_identification) was used to predict prophages, which were then inputted into PHORAGER.

The scripts to install and run PHORAGER's `annotation` module are included below:

# Installation of `annotation` module
phorager install --tools annotation --databases checkv,pharokka,phold

# Run PHORAGER's `annotation` module
phorager annotation --prophage prophage_results/
